&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Intrinsic is an AI robotics group at Google aiming to reimagine the potential of industrial robotics. Our team believes that advances in AI, perception and simulation will redefine what’s possible for industrial robotics in the near future – with software and data at the core.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Our mission is to make industrial robotics intelligent, accessible, and usable for millions more businesses, entrepreneurs, and developers. We are a dynamic team of engineers, roboticists, designers, and technologists who are passionate about unlocking the creative and economic potential of industrial robotics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Administrative Business Partner at Intrinsic, you are the strategic &quot;bridge builder&quot; at the intersection of our Engineering, R&amp;amp;D, and Commercial teams. Supporting three highly collaborative leaders, you act as an Impact Multiplier who synchronizes internal rhythms and serves as a vital liaison for high-stakes external partners and customers. Your mission is to build the &quot;Automated Executive&quot; by using AI and systems thinking to handle the &quot;interruptions&quot; (scheduling, travel, and routine comms), allowing you to focus on the &quot;discretion&quot;—navigating complex stakeholder relationships and preventing strategy collisions before they occur. Unlike a traditional gatekeeper, you are a facilitator who protects leadership bandwidth while ensuring the team remains accessible and mission-aligned.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;How your work moves the mission forward&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Synchronize High-Collaboration Teams:&lt;/strong&gt; Connect the dots between Engineering, R&amp;amp;D, and Commercial workstreams to ensure operational alignment, drive project momentum, and prevent organizational bottlenecks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage High-Stakes External Relationships:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the professional surrogate and key liaison for industrial partners and enterprise customers, managing complex communications and ensuring external stakeholders feel heard and prioritized.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Optimize Executive Bandwidth:&lt;/strong&gt; Leverage Google Workspace and modern productivity tools (including Gemini and basic automation) to seamlessly manage complex calendars, travel logistics, and routine business processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proactive Calendar &amp;amp; Energy Shadowing:&lt;/strong&gt; Masterfully analyze upcoming leadership cycles to anticipate conflicts, identify &quot;energy drains,&quot; and resolve logistical bottlenecks 48 hours in advance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Skills you will need to be successful&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Mastery:&lt;/strong&gt; Minimum of 5 years of direct executive support experience in a fast-paced, high-growth technology or engineering environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Multi-Lead Prioritization:&lt;/strong&gt; Proven ability to seamlessly support multiple executives simultaneously, balancing competing priorities with high responsiveness and composure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Liaison &amp;amp; High EQ:&lt;/strong&gt; Exceptional communication skills and political acumen required to manage high-stakes relationships with internal leadership and external enterprise partners with absolute discretion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Thinking &amp;amp; Tech-Savviness:&lt;/strong&gt; Natural ability to identify patterns in organizational friction and leverage technology (like Google Workspace and AI-assisted tools) to streamline administrative workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project &amp;amp; Event Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience organizing large-scale meeting

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Intrinsic is an AI robotics group at Google aiming to reimagine the potential of industrial robotics. Our team believes that advances in AI, perception and simulation will redefine what’s possible for industrial robotics in the near future – with software and data at the core.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Our mission is to make industrial robotics intelligent, accessible, and usable for millions more businesses, entrepreneurs, and developers. We are a dynamic team of engineers, roboticists, designers, and technologists who are passionate about unlocking the creative and economic potential of industrial robotics.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Robotics Systems Engineer, you will build the connection between our web-based software and the physical hardware on the manufacturing floor. You are responsible for ensuring that when an operator interacts with our interface, the robotic system responds instantly and safely, from synchronizing data records to controlling physical signal lights. You will own the entire lifecycle of a command, ensuring it is authorized, recorded, and executed correctly even if the network is unstable. Your work ensures that our software is a reliable and intuitive controller for the next generation of physical automation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;How your work moves the mission forward&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement secure login and identity systems that manage user access levels and ensure only authorized personnel can trigger physical hardware actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the control logic that bridges the web interface to physical hardware components, including status lights, emergency stops, and operator consoles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect resilient data systems that store robot telemetry locally during network outages and synchronize with the cloud once a connection is restored.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the backend infrastructure required to support multi-tenant environments, ensuring strict data isolation and security between different customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design reliable communication pathways between web browsers and hardware controllers to ensure low-latency feedback for the operator.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create detailed audit logs that link every physical hardware action back to a specific, authenticated user for safety and forensic review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Skills you will need to be successful&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional experience designing and implementing granular user permissions and access control levels within a multi-user software environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in interfacing software with physical hardware through digital inputs and outputs (such as controlling lights, switches, or sensors).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in fullstack development, moving comfortably between server-side logic (Python or C++) and client-side web applications (TypeScript).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical experience with network communication protocols used to send data between different pieces of hardware and software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Skills that will differentiate your candidacy&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with industrial communication standards used to talk to factory equipment and hardware controllers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of distributed systems and how to resolve data conflicts with multi user access.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with real-time operating systems or high-performance messaging systems for low-latency control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience building industrial human-machine interfaces or control panels for complex machinery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with modern build and deployment tools (such as Bazel or containerization) to manage complex, multi-compone

