&lt;p&gt;As a Customer Success Engineer, you will partner closely with our customers to drive the end-to-end delivery of complex robotic automation systems. You will contribute to high-impact initiatives across the North America region, from architecting technical solutions to delivering first-of-a-kind production deployments and managing long-term lifecycle success. By both enabling users to fully leverage Intrinsic’s product suite and co-developing software features for our customers, you will accelerate the strategic adoption of next-generation industrial automation in diverse and challenging production environments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;How your work moves the mission forward&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with our customers and other Intrinsic team members to progress engagements against our shared goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conceptualize new industrial robotic automation solutions and scope the path to deliver them into production.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to projects directly by designing, implementing, testing, and maintaining high-quality software based on Intrinsic&#39;s product. Or enable our customers to progress them more independently, by guiding them to apply Intrinsic’s product effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure clarity and alignment around outcomes you own. Owning communication across internal and external stakeholders, with technical and non-technical backgrounds.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a bridge to the wider Intrinsic team to shape our product roadmap and address customer feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Skills you will need to be successful&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Robotics, Mechatronics, Computer Science, or a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of delivering modern industrial automation solutions into production, with a demonstrated ability to navigate ambiguity, debug issues and drive results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;End-to-end understanding of industrial automation systems and the ability to guide customers to scalable solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in modern software development, specifically with C++ and/or Python in a professional environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passion for being part of a forward deployed team that, together with functions like BD and Product, engages closely with our users every day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional fluency in English and a willingness to frequently travel domestically to support customer engagements in the North America region.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Skills that will differentiate your candidacy&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrable experience in one or more of the following areas: industrial robot programming (e.g., Fanuc, KUKA, UR, ABB, Yaskawa), PLC programming (e.g., Beckhoff, Siemens), machine vision or industrial bus systems (especially EtherCAT), virtual commissioning and simulation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cloud-native technologies and distributed systems, including Kubernetes, gRPC, Protobuf, Bazel, and real-time architectures.&lt;/li&

