&lt;h2&gt;How your work moves the mission forward&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate directly with customers/partners to understand their specific use cases and customize reference HMIs to meet their product needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop visually rich, user-friendly web applications that allow non-experts to interact with, monitor, and control industrial robotic workcells.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bridge the technical gap for customers by guiding them through frontend development best practices and helping them eventually own their custom HMI services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate complex features, such as real-time 3D visualizations and process data, partnering seamlessly with backend engineers to wire up new data streams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work hands-on in the lab and in the field with physical robots, hardware, and automation equipment to test and validate your software interfaces.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain an accessible system of reusable frontend components in collaboration with our Design team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Skills you will need to be successful&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of professional experience in frontend web application development and design, with deep expertise in Angular, TypeScript, and Three.js.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building visually rich, user-friendly client-side applications that enable complex interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Backend Confidence: A strong ability to collaborate with backend teams - you should be comfortable navigating codebases in Go, C++, or Python and understanding data structures to trace data flows and unblock frontend integration tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
